    <text id="B1145T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell describes the organization of the 9th Sub-District, including Augusta
                    County (in the 4th Division).</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Headquarters">Head Qrs</abbr> 9<hi rend="super"
                            >th</hi> Sub-<abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt. Brig.
                        Genl'</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-10">March 10<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to report the following arrangement, made in compliance with
                    Circular No. 1 C.S. from your Head Quarters, viz-</p>

                <p>Ninth Sub-District, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></p>

                <p>1<hi rend="super">st</hi> Division Frederick <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> John
                    A. McDonnell <abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr> to be at the
                    office of the Bureau Winchester.</p>

                <p>2<hi rend="super">d</hi> Division Clarke, Page &amp; Warren <abbr
                        expan="Counties">Cos.</abbr> - E. H. Ripley <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.C.</abbr> to be at
                    Berryville, county seat of <hi rend="underline">Clarke</hi> County, at the
                    Courthouse, on the fourth monday of each month, being court day, to remain 2
                    days, or longer if business demands</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <p>To be at Luray County seat of Page County, at the Courthouse on the 15<hi
                        rend="super">th</hi> of each month <add hand="h1" place="inline">for two
                        days</add> or longer if necessary.</p>

                <p>To be at Front Royal County seat of Warren County, on Court day, at the office of
                    the Bureau and at all other times when not at Berryville or Luray as above
                    stated.</p>

                <p>3<hi rend="super">d</hi> Division Shenandoah &amp; Rockingham</p>

                <p>J.T.H. Hall <abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.C.</abbr>
                    will be at Harrisonburg, County seat of Rockingham County at the American Hotel,
                    on the 3<hi rend="super">rd</hi> Monday of each month, being Court day. He will
                    remain two days, or longer if necessary. He will be at his office, Woodstock,
                    county seat of Shenandoah County, the remainder of the month.</p>

                <p>4<hi rend="super">th</hi> Division Augusta &amp; Highland <abbr
                        expan="Counties">Cos.</abbr></p>

                <p>Thos. P. Jackson, <abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                    >A.S.A.C.</abbr> Official at Staunton, county seat Augusta <abbr expan="County"
                        >Co.</abbr> will be at Monterey, <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> seat of
                    Highland County on the 2<hi rend="super">d</hi> Thursday in each month (Court
                    day) and remain as long as necessary - During <pb n="3"/>the rest of the month,
                    to be found at his office in Staunton.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obed.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Servt.</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                            Comr.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
